 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# SMAE Engine Verification\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the resilient extraction of nutritional data from the SMAE PDF using the `SMAEEngine` implementation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add project root to path for imports\n",
    "sys.path.append(\"../..\")\n",
    "\n",
    "from backend.smae_engine.source_code.main import SMAEEngine\n",
    "from google.cloud import bigquery\n",
    "import pandas as pd"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Initialize Engine\n",
    "The engine uses Pydantic-first validation and implements a page-by-page resilient extraction pipeline."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "engine = SMAEEngine()\n",
    "gcs_uri = \"gs://nutritional-data-sources/SMAE.pdf\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Processing PDF: {gcs_uri}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Execute Extraction\n",
    "We will process a small sample of pages (e.g., pages 5-7) to verify the logic and SCD Type 2 insertion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# In a real scenario, we might process the whole PDF, but for verification we limit the scope\n",
    "# Note: The current main.py processes all pages by default if not specified,\n",
    "# or we can modify it to take a page range if needed. \n",
    "# For this verification, we run the main processing loop.\n",
    "\n",
    "results = engine.process_pdf(gcs_uri=gcs_uri)\n",
    "print(f\"Processed {len(results)} food groups/pages.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Verify Results in BigQuery\n",
    "We query the `food_equivalents` table to see the structured data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "client = bigquery.Client()\n",
    "query = \"\"\"\n",
    "SELECT \n",
    "    family_group, \n",
    "    food, \n",
    "    suggested_quantity, \n",
    "    unit, \n",
    "    energy_kcal, \n",
    "    is_active,\n",
    "    ingestion_at\n",
    "FROM `nutritional-partner.nutrimental_information.food_equivalents` \n",
    "LIMIT 10\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "df = client.query(query).to_dataframe()\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Verify Dead Letter Table\n",
    "Check if any pages failed and were logged for manual review."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dlq_query = \"SELECT * FROM `nutritional-partner.nutrimental_information.extraction_dead_letter`\"\n",
    "dlq_df = client.query(dlq_query).to_dataframe()\n",
    "if dlq_df.empty:\n",
    "    print(\"✅ No extraction errors found in DLQ.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"⚠️ Found {len(dlq_df)} errors in DLQ.\")\n",
    "    display(dlq_df)"
   ]
  }
 ],
